post_text: AIS will be using Schools PLP as our core program for instruction grades 1-12. We will start using this program Tuesday, September 8, 2020. Teachers will be sending information to parents and students this week about the process for logging into the program. Faculty/staff are available at school from 9:00am - 2:00pm each school day and are available each evening for 2 hours between 5:00pm-9:00pm. If you have any questions or concerns, please reach out to us at 606-756-2105.

post_text: If you currently home school your children, consider Augusta Independent’s 100% virtual learning option with access to a full and comprehensive online program available for Preschool-12. The program offers a full curriculum for all grade levels and courses, pacing guides, lessons, activities, videos, assessments, interventions, accommodations and so much more. Students will be engaged in personalized and rigorous learning using one of the most effective virtual learning platforms available. For more information or questions, please contact Superintendent Lisa McCane at 606-756-2545 or Principal Robin Kelsch at 606-756-2105.

post_text: The Augusta Independent School District Board of Education will meet next Thursday, July 23, to discuss and approve the 2020-2021 Reopening Plan recommended by the AISD Reopening Team. Please review the preliminary recommendations and the full Reopening Plan will be released next Friday, July 24, to parents and families. Thank you for your continued patience, understanding and support as we carefully design the safest Reopening Plan. We are excited and looking forward to our students and staff returning soon!

Please review the preliminary recommendations and the full Reopening Plan will be released next Friday, July 24, to parents and families. Thank you for your continued patience, understanding and support as we carefully design the safest Reopening Plan. We are excited and looking forward to our students and staff returning soon!

AS A REMINDER:

We have added the ability to collect some student enrollment forms online. The Infinite Campus Online Registration tools that we have added will help to keep families safe and make the registration process easier. More information about the online enrollment forms will be posted in late July.

In order to take advantage of this new feature, we need you to make sure that you have a Campus Parent Portal account.

In order to sign-up for the parent portal, please e-mail Mr. Litteral at timothy.litteral@augusta.kyschools.us. Provide your name and the name of your child/children. Mr. Litteral will then send sign-up information to the parent. Please allow up to one week for a response.

If you already have an account, but cannot remember your password, please e-mail Mr. Litteral to request that be reset.

post_text:
School Reopening Update

Augusta Independent has established a Reopening Team with representation of faculty, staff, parents, students, board members, community members and health professionals. The Reopening Team will meet June 22 and begin the process to develop a Reopening Plan for the 2020-2021 school year. The Reopening Plan will prioritize the health and safety of all students, faculty, staff and families relative to state health guidelines and restrictions.

The Reopening Team will review the health guidelines for schools, parent/staff surveys and the Kentucky Department of Education guidance documents to develop the plan. Augusta Independent School District anticipates releasing the plan in mid-July and school starting on August 24 following the Reopening Plan and state health guidelines.

We appreciate everyone’s understanding, patience and flexibility as the plan is developed with the health and safety of students and staff being the priority.

The Kentucky GVBACK Tuesday 2020, organized by Augusta Independent School District, Robertson County Schools, and Frankfort Independent Schools, are giving back an hour to mobilize one of the coolest student-led education community support projects in the country.

Our teams will volunteer time to help our local churches, nursing homes, food banks, civic organizations, non-profit groups and city officials for causes that will benefit our residents and local communities.

post_text:
School Contact Information During Closure

As of March 31, 2020, Augusta Independent will further reduce the staff in our buildings. The office at the school location will not be regularly staffed. If you need assistance at the school but no one answers your call, you may contact the Board Office at 606-756-2545. The Board Office will be available daily from 10:00 AM - 2:00 PM until further notice.

As a reminder, all staff members have e-mail, which is being checked regularly. Go to https://www.augusta.kyschools.us/staff and click "Submit" to see a list of staff members. Click “Profile” to see a staff member’s e-mail address.

Paper packets can be submitted to teachers by submitting a picture of the work through e-mail, Dojo, etc. For those who would still like to drop off NTI work in the trays in the front entrance to the school, you can do so Monday-Thursday 8:00AM-Noon.

post_text: There will be no K-PREP testing this school year.
shared_text:
KENTUCKYTEACHER.ORG
KDE cancels K-PREP testing for 2019-2020 school year | Kentucky Teacher

Kentucky Department of Education
March 24 at 8:56 PM ·

NEW: We have canceled K-PREP testing for the 2019-20 year due to the COVID-19 crisis.

Kentucky Interim Education Commissioner Kevin C Brown:

“I hope this will help ease some of the anxiety being felt among our families. I want our teachers and schools to concentrate on providing a great education to their students through the NTI Program rather than worry about standardized testing. Let’s end this year strong despite the extra stress COVID-19 has placed on all of us.”

Full story: https://bit.ly/KPREPcanceled

#KyEd #MyNTIKy

The Augusta Independent School Board honored Mr. Robin Kelsch at the March board meeting for his dedication and 17-years of service as a head basketball coach. Mr. Kelsch coached the boys for 13 seasons and the girls 4 seasons and was an assistant coach 6-years prior to being a head coach. Thank you Coach Kelsch for your years of dedication and service to our kids and community! #PantherPride #AtownsFinest #OnceaPantherAlwaysaPanther

Pictured is Superintendent Lisa McCane presenting Coach Robin Kelsch a plaque.

FITNESS CENTER UPDATE
Due to school being closed through April 12 and the KHSAA declaring a dead-period through the same period in response to COVID-19, the fitness center will be closed to ALL individuals through April 12. Based on current information, it is expected the fitness center will re-open April 13. For those who have paid membership dues for the month of March, you will be given complimentary membership for the remainder of April. Thank you for your understanding.

post_text: Congratulations to our high school academic team members who placed in the written assessment on Saturday at the District Governor's Cup competition! Carter Buerkley placed 5th in Science, Aubree Ruf tied for 4th in Arts and Humanities, and Serenity Blevins tied for 3rd in Language Arts. These students will compete at the regional competition on February 15.

post_text:
The Kentucky Board of Education is inviting residents and stakeholders to take a community survey on the qualities they would like to see in the state’s next education commissioner.

The survey, available at the link below, will close at 5 p.m. on Feb. 6. It takes about five minutes to complete. The board hopes to have a new commissioner in place by July 1.

https://www.surveymonkey.com/r/2020CommissionerSearch
